      <h1>EMERGENCIES</h1>
      <p>We can assist Swedish nationals who find themselves in difficulty while in Glasgow or south west Scotland.</p>
      <p>If you are seriously ill or injured, are the victim of a crime, or face other difficult personal circumstances then we can provide help and advice.</p>
      <p>During business hours, Monday to Friday, call: 0141 204 4041</p>
      <p class="short-line">Outside business hours call:</p>
      <p class="short-line">- David Hunter, Consul: 07767 432203, or</p>
      <p class="short-line">- Mairi Murray, Consular Assistant: 07563 950 908</p>
      <p class="short-line">Please note: these numbers are for <span class="strong-text">emergencies only</span>.</p>
      <h2 style="padding-top: 32px;">EMERGENCY PASSPORTS</h2>
      <p>The Glasgow consulate can issue emergency passports – see <a href="passports" class="passports-link">PASSPORTS</a> for advice.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

